DevelopmentAddress: Wilton Shopping Centre , located to the south of Bishopstown Road , to the East of Cardinal Way
ApplicantAddress: 2nd Floor Block E , Iveagh Court , Harcourt, Dublin 2
DevelopmentDescription: Permission for a mixed use development at Wilton Shopping Centre on a site of 4.82 hectares which is located to the south of Bishopstown Road, to the east of Cardinal way and to the west of Sarsfield Road at Wilton, Cork City. The proposed development consists of: the partial demolition of the existing shopping centre [including the Pennys anchor store located at 56 Homefront] located to the northern end of the existing shopping centre comprising an area of 4,222m2 and the removal of 420 surface car parking spaces. The proposed development also consists of the construction of an extension to the existing shopping centre ranging in height from two to seven stories. The proposed extension consists of: Retail and retail services [including cafe/restaurant uses] over three levels compromising 21,223m2 GFA,a 14 screen [1.550 seats], cinema compromising 4,165m2 GFA, offices compromising 4,398m2 GFA, a 190 no. bedroom hotel compromising 9,335m2 GFA, a public plaza and outdoor seating area, a multi storey car park with 6 levels providing 874 spaces, a surface car park on the roof of the second storey which is accessed from the multi storey car park providing 257 spaces and the replacement of 178 surface car parking spaces as well as 227 bike parking spaces and 70 motorbike parking spaces. Also proposed is a new vehicular entrance/egress from Sarsfield Road, as well as the relocation of the existing pedestrian crossing further north on Sarsfield Road. In addition, dedicated floorspace for landlord areas is proposed, including food court seating, toilets, shared cores, general circulation areas and corridors. The total gross area to be constructed of all levels is 66,681m2. Permission is sought for the outlined herein including, but not limited to, works in existing accesses, plant areas, ESB substations and mechanical and electrical switchrooms , landscaping and all associated site works. An Environmental Impact Assessment Report [EIAR formerly known as EIS] has been prepared and will be submitted to the Planning Authority with the application

DevelopmentDescription: Trigon Hotels Ltd, intend to apply for a 10-year permission for full planning permission for the redevelopment and refurbishment of the Metropole Hotel and former P.J. O' Hea site at a site bounded by MacCurtain Street to the north, St. Patrick's Quay to the south and existing buildings to the east and west; Harley's Street traverses the centre of the site. The proposed development consists of 1) the demolition of buildings to the south of the original  Metropole hotel including the modern existing rear extension, Leeside Leisure, and part of No. 25 St Patrick's Quay (the fa�ade of No. 25 St. Patrick's Quay is to be kept and incorporated into the hotel redevelopment) and 2) the demolition of the former P.J. O' Hea building St Patrick's Quay and Harley's Street. The proposed development includes the construction of a new hotel extension of 6 floors over upper & lower ground level to the south of the existing  Metropole Hotel with primary access from the existing MacCurtain Street Hotel entrance at Ground Floor level. It includes hotel accommodation of 140 new bedrooms, bar and restaurant facilities, 4 no. retail / cafe units at ground floor level, penthouse function rooms, 2 levels of basement parking for 92 cars, ancillary hotel uses and site access and development works. The refurbishment and renovation of the existing hotel building includes 43 bedroom suites and meeting rooms, the rein-statement of original ground floor frontage and the historic entrance on MacCurtain Street. The proposed development also allows for the construction of a new 228 bedroom hotel at the former P.J. O' Hea site consisting of 6 floors of bedroom accommodation over upper and lower ground floor lobby and including hotel bar with one retail unit, roof terrace and two no. link bridges to the Metropole Hotel over Harley's Street. The proposed overall development will allow for a total of 411 no. bedrooms. Access to the car park is via St. Patrick's Quay. The proposed development includes signage and all associated site development works. This application is accompanied by a Natura Impact Statement (NIS) and Environmental Impact Statement (EIS) / Environmental Impact Assessment Report (EIAR) The Metropole Hotel is a protected structure (Cork City Council Record of Protected Structures listing PS 185)

Additional proposals (alterations to existing roads (Albert Quay East to commencement of Victoria Road) relate to an area of 0.076ha.  The site is bounded to the east by Idle Hour public house and the rear of the properties fronting Victoria Road, to the west by Carey Tool Hire and to the South by the rear of properties fronting Albert Road. DevelopmentDescription: Development at 1.55ha site consisting of building/structures bounded by Victoria Rd, Kennedy Quay, Marina Walk & a road to the west of the Odlums complex(Furlong Rd), South Docks, Cork City. The development consists of the demolition of the two R&H Hall grain silos between Kennedy Quay & Marina Walk,  a former office building on the corner of Kennedy Quay & Victoria Road, a former laboratory building on Victoria Road, an electricity substation & boundary walls. It is proposed to erect two buildings on the cleared site, namely Block A1(to be known as �One Kennedy Quay�) & Block A2(to be known as �The Furlong Building�) & form a new street (to be known as �Navigation Street�) between them that will link Kennedy Quay & Marina Walk.  Block A1, at the western end of the site, will have, over basement level, a gross floor area of 25,130sqm & be variously 7 to 8 storeys high (30.6m to 33.7mOD to parapet). It will comprise a gym (350sqm), a caf�/deli (270sqm), a convenience store (400sqm), 2 no bar/restaurants (totalling 1105sqm), 3 no general office units (totalling 1585sqm), an enclosed service yard & 2 no electricity substations at ground floor level.  The upper floors will comprise a cr�che (215sqm) at first floor level & 165 no apartments (23 no one bedroom; 97 no two bedroom & 45 no three bedroom units). A semi private courtyard open space to serve the apartments & outdoor cr�che play area are proposed at first floor level.  Block A2, at the eastern end of the site, will comprise general office uses & will have, over basement level, a gross floor area of 25, 892sqm (including 1 no electricity switch room) & be variously 7 to 11 storeys high (31.75m to 46.0m OD to parapet). The development proposes a 2 storey basement to accommodate a car park with vehicular access & egress from Navigation St via a ramp access serving a total of 413 car parking spaces as well as cycle storage, storage & plant areas. It is also proposed to raise ground levels to +4.0mOD & form retaining walls, carry out public realm works (including ventilation ducts) & landscaping, install & connect to services & form public & private open space. All storeys numbers quoted above are over 2 new basement floor levels & building heights quoted are over datum(OD). Existing surrounding road levels are approximately +2.6 to 2.8mOD(Kennedy Quay), +2.2 to 2.8OD(Victoria Rd), +2.3 to 3.0mOD(Marina Walk). DevelopmentAddress: Cork University Hospital  , Bishopstown Road , Wilton
ApplicantAddress: Beacon Hall , The Mall , Beacon Court, Sandyford Dublin 18
DevelopmentDescription: For development of a proposed co-located private hospital at the Cork University Hospital. The co-located hospital site is located in the north-eastern corner of the CUH Campus, and principally bounded to the north by the residential properties of Wilton Gardens and Laburnum Park; to the South by the existing Mental Health Services Unit and the UCC Clinical Sciences Department of CUH; to the east by the residential properties of Wilton Road and Congress Place; and to the west by existing Ambulatory Services. The development will consist of: the provision of a new two to five storey over double basement 185 no. bedroom hospital (comprising 175 no. in-patient beds and 10 no. ICU/HDU/CCU beds) including the following clinical uses: oncology, physiotherapy, operating theatres, consultant suites, day procedure suite, research and education area with clinical and non-clinical support areas, which will be linked to, and integrated with, the existing hospital via a pedestrian walkway at first floor level. The development will also include the provision of a new two level decked car park, located in the west of the CUH Campus, comprising 320 no. car parking spaces (of which 160 no. are replacement car parking spaces); the provision of two basement levels comprising 511 no. car parking spaces (of which 230 no. are replacement car parking spaces); 42 no. surface car parking spaces; 102 no. bicycle spaces at basement and surface levels. The total gross floor area of the development is 32,893 sq m (excluding basements). The development will also include the reconfiguration of the existing main hospital entrance on Bishopstown Road and the creation of a new slip road egress; revisions to the internal road layout; boundary treatments, services provision; the provision of a new MV sub-station, a waste compound, an oxygen and gas compound, the removal and relocation of the existing ESB substation and switch room; ancillary retail, cafe restaurant and storage accommodation; plant; changes in level; associated signage and ramps/access barriers, hard and soft landscaping; minor reconfiguration works at the interfaces between the existing hospital and the proposed new link and all other necessary site development and excavation works above and below ground.
